wmcpuwatch: wmcpuwatch (dockapp that shows CPU load)
wmcpuwatch:
wmcpuwatch: wmcpuwatch is a WindowMaker dockapp which aims to show the load of
wmcpuwatch: every logical CPU on the system.
wmcpuwatch:
wmcpuwatch: It is a fork of wmmon. wmmon shows the load of up to 10 CPUs. With
wmcpuwatch: a little tweaking it is possible to show 12 with wmmon, but when in
wmcpuwatch: 2017 Intel announced an 18 core CPU (and AMD was with their Ryzen even
wmcpuwatch: earlier), then it was time for a new dockapp.
